Das Mehrebenenmodell

\(\hat{y}\) \(=\) \(a+bx\)

\(\hat{y}\) \(=\) \(a\) \(+\) \(b\) \(x\)

\(\hat{y}\) \(=\) \(\beta_0\) \(+\) \(\beta_1\) \(x_1\)

\(\hat{y}\) \(=\) \(\beta_0\) \(+\) \(\beta_1\) \(x_1 ~+~ ...~ \beta_nx_n\)

\(y\) \(\ne\) \(\hat{y}\)

\(y\) \(=\) \(\hat{y}\) \(+\) \(e\)

\(y\) \(=\) \(\beta_0+\beta_1x_1\) \(+~...~\beta_nx_n~+~\) \(e\)
